    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n847" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀναγκαῖος</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">η, ον</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνάγκη</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">constraining;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μῦθος</span>, command ‘of force,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 17.399</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρειώ</span>, ‘dire’ need, <i><span class="en">Il.
            8.57</span></i>; esp. with reference to slavery, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἦμαρ ἀναγκαῖον</span> (= <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δούλιον
            ἦμαρ</span>), <i><span class="en">Il. 16.836</span></i>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δμῶες ἀναγκαῖοι</span>, ‘bond’ servants,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 24.210</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; πολεμισταί</span>, warriors ‘perforce,’
            <i><span class="en">Od. 24.499</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
